theorem interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior
        (closure
          (interior
            (closure
              (interior
                (closure
                  (interior
                    (closure
                      (interior
                        (closure (A : Set X))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, compress the innermost six iterations using the existing lemma.
  have h₁ :
      interior
        (closure
          (interior
            (closure
              (interior
                (closure
                  (interior
                    (closure (A : Set X)))))))) =
        interior (closure A) := by
    simpa using
      (interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_eq
        (A := A))
  -- Rewrite the target with `h₁` and apply the basic two-step simplification.
  calc
    interior
        (closure
          (interior
            (closure
              (interior
                (closure
                  (interior
                    (closure
                      (interior
                        (closure (A : Set X))))))))) =
        interior
          (closure
            (interior
              (closure (A : Set X)))) := by
          simpa [h₁]
    _ = interior (closure A) := by
          simpa using
            (interior_closure_interior_closure_eq (A := A))
